BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 3.088018 Tw (Modern systems present themselves as secure through layered authentication mechanisms, including) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.433631 Tw (passwords, two-factor authentication, multi-factor authentication, device verification, and biometric login.) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.10961 Tw (These mechanisms are widely implemented, actively maintained, and genuinely effective at restricting access) Tj T* 0 Tw .262545 Tw (to recognised identities. They represent a significant investment in security infrastructure \227 and they are not) Tj T* 0 Tw (the problem.) Tj T* ET
