.058824 .098039 .137255 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 70.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 2.374079 Tw (The problem is what they are assumed to do beyond their actual function. These mechanisms create) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.752442 Tw (confidence that system access is controlled and, by extension, that system behaviour is legitimate. This) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.525799 Tw (assumption is incorrect. Authentication verifies identity. It does not verify whether an action should occur) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.910723 Tw (under current conditions. These are different questions, addressed by different mechanisms, at different) Tj T* 0 Tw (moments \227 and conflating them creates a governance gap that security investment cannot close.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
